But when \(N \to \infty,\) \(\sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{n!} = e - 2,\) \(\frac{1}{(N + 1)!} \to 0,\) \(\frac{1}{(N + 2)!} \to 0.\) Thus, \[\sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{n^2 + n - 1}{(n + 2)!} = e - 2.\]
